    "themes": ["christ_central", "cross", "resurrection", "assurance"],\
    "scripture_refs": ["Philippians 3:8-10", "Romans 8:31-39", "1 Corinthians 15:54-57"],\
    "summary_theology": "This modern hymn walks through the life, death, and resurrection of Christ and the security believers have in Him. It is rich in doctrine, touching on atonement, victory over death, and unshakable hope. The song keeps Christ at the center and leaves worshipers with a deep sense of confidence in His finished work.",\
    "practical_worship_leadership": "This can anchor a more theologically focused service and works well in communion, Easter, or Reformation type gatherings. It also bridges traditional and modern styles which can help unite different generations. Encourage people to really listen as they sing so the story sinks beyond the melody.",\
    "arrangement_tips": "You can lead this with a very simple accompaniment or with a full band that still leaves space for voices. The triple meter can feel unfamiliar for some, so keep the tempo steady and supportive. Call and response on a verse or two can draw in those who are newer to the song.",\
    "tags": ["modern_hymn", "doctrinal", "cross_centered", "intergenerational"]\
  \},\
  \{\
    "slug": "the-lion-and-the-lamb",\
    "title": "The Lion And The Lamb",\
    "primary_artist": "Bethel Music",\
    "default_male_key": "B",\
    "default_female_key": "D",\
    "tempo_bpm": 90,\
    "time_signature": "4/4",\
    "themes": ["kingship", "victory", "cross-and-crown"],\
    "scripture_refs": ["Revelation 5:5-6", "Philippians 2:9-11"],\
    "summary_theology": "This song declares Jesus as both the conquering Lion and the sacrificial Lamb. It highlights His authority over all nations and His victory through humility and the cross. The contrasts in the language help the church remember that the King we worship rules through self giving love.",\
    "practical_worship_leadership": "Use this when you want to focus your church on the lordship of Christ and the hope of His return. It can serve as a strong up tempo song in the middle of a set that emphasizes His rule. Invite people to consider areas of life that need to bow to Jesus as they sing.",\
    "arrangement_tips": "Lock the groove with the drummer and bass so the song feels strong but not rushed. Guitars can carry the main riffs but watch volume so vocals remain clear. Consider ending with a repeated chorus that gradually simplifies instrumentally to let the church carry it out.",\
    "tags": ["modern", "kingship", "victory", "upbeat"]\
  \},\
  \{\
    "slug": "how-great-is-our-god",\
    "title": "How Great Is Our God",\
    "primary_artist": "Chris Tomlin",\
    "default_male_key": "G",\
    "default_female_key": "Bb",\
    "tempo_bpm": 76,\
    "time_signature": "4/4",\
    "themes": ["greatness-of-god", "trinity", "praise"],\
    "scripture_refs": ["Psalm 104:1-2", "1 Chronicles 29:11"],\
    "summary_theology": "This classic modern worship song exalts the greatness of God, referencing His eternal nature, strength, and beauty. It hints at Trinitarian language and lifts up the name of Jesus among the nations. The simplicity of the lyric makes it easy for all ages to sing together while still pointing to deep truths.",\
    "practical_worship_leadership": "This is an anchor song that can be used almost anywhere in a gathering. It works well when your church needs a familiar moment or when you want a simple declaration everyone can grab. Invite older saints to sing out and let the younger ones feel the weight of a song that has served the church for years.",\
    "arrangement_tips": "It can be led very simply or with a full band, but the key is to keep the melody out front and singable. Resist the urge to over complicate it with too many tags. A key change can serve the room if it is not forced.",\
    "tags": ["modern_classic", "praise", "intergenerational", "flexible"]\
  \},\
  \{\
    "slug": "the-blessing",\
    "title": "The Blessing",\
    "primary_artist": "Kari Jobe & Cody Carnes",\
    "default_male_key": "Bb",\
    "default_female_key": "D",\
    "tempo_bpm": 72,\
    "time_signature": "4/4",\
    "themes": ["blessing", "generations", "favor", "presence"],\
    "scripture_refs": ["Numbers 6:24-26", "Deuteronomy 7:9"],\
